article_title: Father travels cross-country to search for son Daniel Robinson missing from Arizona job site since June
meta_description: Daniel Robinson, 24, was last seen on June 23, 2021, driving his 2017 blue Jeep Renegade with Arizona license plate NLA2CMA as he left his job site in the desert area west of Sun Valley Parkway just north of Cactus Road in Buckeye, Arizona. Investigators said a ping was established on his cell phone but no location data was available due to the phone being off or out of range. It did not appear he'd made any calls or texts after leaving the site. Neither his car nor his phone has been found. The Buckeye Police Department in Arizona is investigating.

article_title: Pam Hupp charged with first degree murder in 2011 stabbing death of Betsy Faria
meta_description: Pam Hupp has been charged with first degree murder in the 2011 death of Betsy Faria in Lincoln County, Missouri. Pam was the last person to see Betsy alive before she was stabbed to death at her home on December 27, 2011. Just days before Betsy was killed, she made Pam the sole beneficiary of her $150,000 life insurance policy. Betsyâs husband, Russ Faria, was initially charged and convicted of his wifeâs murder. But the conviction was later overturned. The focus shifted to Pam Hupp who was convicted of killing Louis Gumpenberger in 2016. That case prompted Lincoln County Prosecuting Attorney Mike Wood to reopen Betsy Faria's murder case.
